## Copilot / AI Agent Instructions — nexcent

This is a small Next.js app-router project using TypeScript, TailwindCSS (v4), and `pnpm`.

- Project entry: the app uses the `app/` router. Global layout and fonts live in [app/layout.tsx](app/layout.tsx).
- Package manager & scripts: use `pnpm`. Common commands: `pnpm dev`, `pnpm build`, `pnpm start`, `pnpm lint` (see [package.json](package.json)).
- Styling: Tailwind v4 + PostCSS configured; global styles at [app/globals.css](app/globals.css).

Architecture & patterns (what matters)

- Server components by default: files under `app/` are server components unless they start with `"use client"`. Prefer server components for layout and static UI; convert to client when using hooks or browser APIs. Example: [app/components/Header.tsx](app/components/Header.tsx) uses `"use client"` and `usePathname()` to set active links.
- Fonts and providers: centralize fonts/providers in [app/layout.tsx](app/layout.tsx) using `next/font/google` to avoid duplicate downloads.
- UI organization: shared UI lives in [app/components/](app/components/). Small presentational components use explicit TypeScript props (see [app/components/FeatureCard.tsx](app/components/FeatureCard.tsx)).

Assets & Images

- Static assets belong in `public/`. Prefer absolute paths (e.g. `/logo.svg`) when referencing public assets from components, or use static imports for optimization. Components commonly use `next/image` for optimized images.

Integration & infra notes

- There are no API routes in the repo. If adding backend endpoints, add route handlers under `app/api/` (app-router style).
- `next.config.ts` is minimal — recommend conservative changes and include rationale in PR descriptions.

Developer workflows & checks

- Run dev: `pnpm dev` (Next runs on :3000 by default).
- Build and type-check: `pnpm build` will run Next's build (includes TypeScript checks).
- Lint: `pnpm lint` (configured via `eslint.config.mjs`).

Conventions to follow

- Keep changes focused: update only the files relevant to the task (UI → `app/components/*`, routing → `app/*`).
- When introducing client behavior, add `"use client"` at file top and keep client logic minimal.
- Prefer explicit TypeScript interfaces for component props and export shared types from `app/components/` or a `types/` file if added.

Examples from this repo

- Active nav example: [app/components/Header.tsx](app/components/Header.tsx) uses `usePathname()` to toggle `font-bold` for active routes.
- Presentational component example: [app/components/FeatureCard.tsx](app/components/FeatureCard.tsx) declares a `FeatureCardProps` interface and uses `next/image`.

Where to look first

- Layout and global CSS: [app/layout.tsx](app/layout.tsx) and [app/globals.css](app/globals.css)
- Page entry: [app/page.tsx](app/page.tsx)
- Shared UI: [app/components/](app/components/)
- Scripts & deps: [package.json](package.json)

